questionText: The Ramsar convention aims to conserve wetland habitats.
author: AGA1PIIWM8I8D

questionText: Industrialization reduces the amounts of wetland acreage.
author: A2IXBTOWQRCLPZ

questionText: Pieces of land that remain underwater for part of the year are called wetlands.
author: A22I5RTLJTY3JZ

questionText: The U.S. loses 70 to 100 thousand acres of wetlands every year.
author: A22I5RTLJTY3JZ

questionText: Human development is contributing to wetland destruction.
author: A22I5RTLJTY3JZ

questionText: In the US, the Army Corps of Engineers has retreated from enforcing the main law protecting wetlands.
author: A2IXBTOWQRCLPZ

questionText: The Army Corps of Engineers incorporated stricter regulations on protecting wetlands by 2000.
author: A22I5RTLJTY3JZ
